WEBVTT

00:00.015 --> 00:01.447
<i>Previously on "Heartland"...</i>

00:01.717 --> 00:03.284
What happened
with the restructuring?

00:03.352 --> 00:04.952
Bedford Oil is history.

00:05.020 --> 00:07.154
- What?
- Now there's nothing to stop me

00:07.222 --> 00:08.689
from being here with you.

00:08.756 --> 00:10.757
I don't think that I can
live like this anymore.

00:10.825 --> 00:13.226
- What're you saying?
- I think I wanna go back to school.

00:13.294 --> 00:14.361
Okay, yeah.

00:14.429 --> 00:16.730
Tim's selling
Big River Ranch.

00:16.798 --> 00:19.132
But there's this kid, Shane,
staying at the dude ranch

00:19.200 --> 00:21.100
and he really wants
to go riding.

00:21.168 --> 00:23.537
Wow! It's like you were
born on a saddle.

00:23.604 --> 00:24.804
You know,
your boy's a natural.

00:24.871 --> 00:26.939
I'm not here
to relive the past, Tim.

00:27.006 --> 00:28.106
<i>I'm just here</i>
<i>because I...</i>

00:28.174 --> 00:29.475
Because why?

00:29.543 --> 00:31.444
I want my son to know
who his father is.

00:38.051 --> 00:39.084
Oh...

00:40.019 --> 00:41.118
(Sighs heavily)

00:45.924 --> 00:47.325
(Horse whinnies)

00:51.864 --> 00:54.332
(Hooves thud in the snow,
horses whinny)

01:01.506 --> 01:03.640
Amy: You know, it's nice that you
get to stay a little longer.

01:03.708 --> 01:06.243
Shane: Yeah. My mom changed
her mind about leaving.

01:06.310 --> 01:07.778
That's great.

01:08.713 --> 01:11.582
Actually, I got a theory
about this whole thing.

01:11.649 --> 01:13.816
Yeah? What's that?

01:13.884 --> 01:16.252
Well... well, you know,
it's just a theory.

01:16.319 --> 01:18.755
Okay.
You gonna tell me?

01:18.822 --> 01:20.490
Mmm... ah, no.

01:20.557 --> 01:22.358
No, it might be kinda dumb.

01:22.426 --> 01:24.093
Hey, can we start
our riding lesson?

01:24.160 --> 01:26.128
I think I'm getting
pretty good, right?

01:26.196 --> 01:27.263
Well, you do have
a good teacher.

01:27.698 --> 01:29.297
(Truck rumbles)

01:34.804 --> 01:36.905
<i>(Truck idles loudly outside)</i>

01:38.173 --> 01:40.509
<i>(Dog barks in the distance)</i>

01:42.311 --> 01:44.879
(Engine turns off,
truck doors open and close)

01:44.946 --> 01:46.046
Oh no!

01:47.382 --> 01:48.482
No!

01:51.185 --> 01:53.220
(Hooves thud heavily)

01:59.528 --> 02:01.528
Lisa: I'd like you to
meet Bonnie and Clyde.

02:01.595 --> 02:03.329
Aren't they
the most gorgeous animals?

02:03.397 --> 02:05.432
Jack: Look at these guys.
Lisa: Yeah.

02:05.499 --> 02:06.966
<i>Jack:</i> <i>What do you
think there,</i> <i>Shane?</i>

02:07.034 --> 02:08.668
<i>Shane:</i>
<i>Awesome!</i>

02:08.735 --> 02:10.836
The biggest horses
I've ever seen.

02:10.905 --> 02:12.338
<i>Lisa:</i>
<i>They're Clydesdales,</i>

02:12.406 --> 02:15.074
and they are pulling
the lead float

02:15.142 --> 02:17.342
at the Hudson Winter Fair.

02:17.410 --> 02:19.344
Aren't they a nice match?

02:19.412 --> 02:21.046
They're pretty awesome.

02:21.113 --> 02:22.614
Shoulda seen the deal
I got on them.

02:22.682 --> 02:24.282
Yeah, I'm sure.

02:24.350 --> 02:25.751
No, really!

02:25.819 --> 02:27.052
Although, Amy,
I was wondering

02:27.119 --> 02:28.153
if you could work with them
just a little bit

02:28.220 --> 02:29.254
to get them used
to pulling the sleigh.

02:30.924 --> 02:33.257
What,
they're not trained yet?

02:33.325 --> 02:35.125
You didn't buy 'em
'cause they're pretty?

02:35.193 --> 02:36.828
No, but the owner did say

02:36.895 --> 02:38.796
that they have a few
little behavioral issues.

02:38.864 --> 02:40.498
Other than that
they're perfect together.

02:40.566 --> 02:42.232
Did they happen to say
what those issues are?

02:42.300 --> 02:44.401
Um...He said they're kind of
like an old married couple,

02:44.470 --> 02:46.170
kind of bicker
now and again.

02:46.237 --> 02:47.605
But other than that

02:47.673 --> 02:49.238
they basically can't live
without each other.

02:49.306 --> 02:50.807
What do you think?
Are you game?

02:50.875 --> 02:52.075
I would love
to work with them!

02:52.142 --> 02:53.276
I gotta show, Ty.
This is cool!

02:55.546 --> 02:58.381
Amy: Ty?! Hey, you gotta come
see these horses Lisa bought.

02:58.449 --> 03:00.717
I slept in!
I'm gonna be late for my exam.

03:00.785 --> 03:01.952
Well, they're Clydesdales.

03:02.019 --> 03:03.019
She asked me
to train them for her

03:03.087 --> 03:04.420
for the Winter Fair parade.

03:04.488 --> 03:05.554
You could help me.

03:05.622 --> 03:07.356
We could maybe work
on this together.

03:07.423 --> 03:09.024
Uh... sounds good.

03:09.092 --> 03:10.659
I... I gotta go, Amy.

03:10.727 --> 03:13.061
If there's any traffic
on the freeway, I'm done.

03:13.129 --> 03:14.129
Good luck!

03:14.197 --> 03:15.163
<i>Ty:</i>
<i>Thank you!</i>

03:15.231 --> 03:16.732
(Phone beeps)

03:16.800 --> 03:18.233
<i>Amy:</i>
<i>Ty! You forgot your phone!</i>

03:18.301 --> 03:19.401
(Phone beeps)

